Microtech Lightfoot-L.C.C. D/A (hidden spring released by sliding thumb but is impossible to find unless you know it's there)
12/2000 date/// serial number in the low two thousands

This is an original Microtech that was hand made in Vero Beach, Florida before the company was sold to the Microtech company you know today. It was a Christmas gift from my mother who took my brother and I to the small factory and got to watch the owner build it in front of us, so instead of carrying it daily I never left home with it because I didn't want to loose it. I loved watching the faces of my friends because they could not figure out how I magically opened the blade without moving my hand.  

It has a lifetime warranty that is transferable to the new owner. I actually just took advantage of the warranty and sent it to them so they could sharpen the blade and make sure it's in perfect condition to be sold. This particular knife is a collectors item because it was one of the last ones made by hand. If you are a knife collector you won't want to pass this opportunity up because you will probably never see a Microtech that was handmade by the original owner again.

Asking $500 O.B.O.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Remington Model 10 Pump Shotgun
postcontent: Gun is a Remington Model 10 Pump Shotgun, serial #U55324, made around 1908, discontued making them in 1929.  Total production was 275,600.  It is a 12 gauge, one of the earlier ones before they put the model 10 on the gun, but Remington has told me that any serial number beginning in U were the early ones.  There were about 6 other serial numbers after that.  The bluing is all original but a little faded, there is no bare metal, wood is in great shape with the exception there is one hair line crack behind the receiver.  For as old as the gun is, it is in very good shape.  The bore looks to be good.  I will trade this for a revolver, either a Smith, Colt, or Ruger.  I am looking for something for conceal and carry.  Will trade up or down.  This gun is a real collectible gun.

title: For Sale/Trade:  “No Gunsmith” Scope Kits for Marlin and Henry CF Rifles
location: 3960 Palmer Park Blvd, Col Spgs, CO, Colorado Springs, Colorado
postcontent:
March 12th & 13th at the Prospectors Sertoma Gun Show located in the beautiful NEW Colorado Springs Event Center in Rustic Hills at 3960 Palmer Park Blvd, Colorado Springs, CO. (NE corner of Palmer Park Blvd and Academy Blvd in central Colorado Springs.)

We install and test mounts, rings, hardware and scopes from specialty suppliers on Marlin rifles to develop the best combination of scopes, mounts and rings at equitable prices.

Kit components are purchased from Aim Sports, New Century, Leapers, TRW, Fastenal and other sources. In some cases, when we can’t find a fully satisfactory mount, we modify the mount hardware to improve the function and quality of the application.

All of our kits are “No Gunsmith” which means there is no drilling, tapping, grinding, cutting, bolt bending, or modifications to your rifle required to mount the hardware. In some cases, an installation might require the removal of a factory sight. Allen wrenches are included with some mounts, but you may need a screwdriver, wrench or some simple hand tools to complete the installation. All installations are completely reversible to restore the rifle to its original configuration.

The following listed scope kits use aircraft quality aluminum Picatinny rails fitted to Marlin Flat Top receivers which are used on most Marlin and Henry center fire rifles. The Picatinny rail attaches to the receiver with steel screws. Medium height one inch aluminum rings secure the scope to the Picatinny Rail.

All of the scopes we sell have lifetime warranties from the respective manufacturers. Mounts, rings and misc. hardware are warranted by us for 90 days.

These scope kits fit the following Marlin (and Marlin style) rifles:
